[{"id": "30dab0e0-6323-4a17-b3a5-997eed350eda", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: thursday noon. kelly sits alone in the canteen listening to outlander on her bluetooth bose headphones. A boy is occasionally throwing food at her from the table in front of her. A teacher sees this going on. kelly looks up at the teacher but he keeps walking. a pea bounces off her forehead. just then kelly looks up and sees a girl standing in the doorway. Long legs, c-cups, dark hair, this girl is beautiful. boys are taking notice. she lowers her sunglasses and spots the food line and walks toward it. hips swinging naturally, not overdone. \n\nkelly feels herself flushing and puts her head down to eat. another pea bounces off her head. \n\nshe chances a look up and the girl is looking around for a place to sit, tray in hand. she spots kelly sitting alone and starts to walk toward her\nASSISTANT: \nThursday noon. Canteen noise fades behind my Bose headphones. Davina Porter's voice fills my ears as Claire Fraser touches the standing stones for the first time. Something wet hits my forehead. A pea. I don't look up.\n\nThe food-throwing continues. Rhythmic. Annoying. A teacher walks past, eyes forward, mouth set in a line of indifference. Another pea bounces off my hair. I keep chewing. The potatoes are bland today. Better than last Tuesday's mystery meat.\n\nMovement catches my peripheral vision. A girl in the doorway. Long legs. Dark hair falling past her shoulders. Boys at nearby tables turn. She lowers sunglasses, scans the room, then walks toward the food line. Hips sway with each step. Natural. Not exaggerated.\n\nHeat creeps up my neck. I duck my head, focusing on my plate. Another pea hits my scalp. When I risk a glance, she's holding a tray, scanning for a seat. Her eyes find mine. She starts walking toward my table.", "embedding": [-0.010426959954202175, -0.038316190242767334, 0.1088566780090332, -0.02471703104674816, 0.0285091083496809, -0.04527740180492401, 0.10873866826295853,